## Overview  
**Dr. Elizabeth Hinton** is an acclaimed historian and scholar specializing in African American history, mass incarceration, and the racial dynamics of the U.S. criminal justice system. She is widely recognized for her groundbreaking research on the origins of mass incarceration and the impact of federal policies on Black communities in the post-civil rights era.

