## Impact & Legacy  

Dr. Elizabeth Hinton’s scholarship has significantly impacted the national dialogue on race and policing, challenging policymakers and academics to reconsider the historical origins of mass incarceration and its devastating effects on Black communities.

**Africana Studies Relation:**  
Her work bridges history, public policy, and Africana Studies by critically examining the systemic injustices faced by African Americans and offering insights into avenues for social justice reform.

